> bas"and looking to all said "SOOOO... What have in common Rodimus, Cyclonus,
> and Cryoteck's generals? They must have something in common, and knowing
> that we will know who is behind this mess..."

<NEW>

Even as HYDRAS was asking the questions the door to his meeting
chamber slid open, the sound of a dark chuckling could be heard just
outside the door. "Perhaps you need to understand just where CRYOTEK's
generals came from first."

In walked TARANTULUS carrying a PADD in his hand. He looked at HYDRAS
and then at the others in the room coming to a stop on CRYOTEK. "Tell
them Cryotek! Tell them where you got your generals from. Or I will"

There was a pause as the room tempeture began to drop as CRYOTEK
turned to face TARANULUS, his optic glowing danergously - he only had
one real one, the other being a mechanical replacement. "You had
better tell your underlings how to address their betters before I have
to put him in his place."

TARANTULUS smiled seemingly not in the slightest bit fazed by CRYOTEK.
"You threaten me because you know the answer to my question, and you
know what it means." He slammed his PADD down on the table.

CRYOTEK stood up his wings flaring out behind him.

(TAG)

Preston
